```C++
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>>& shiftGrid(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int k) {
        int rows = grid.size(), cols = grid[0].size(), n = rows*cols; 
        int r = gcd(n,k);
        for(int i = 0; i<r;i++) {
            int temp = grid[i/cols][i%cols];
            int curr_idx = i;
            for(int j = 0;j<n/r;j++) {
                int next_idx = (curr_idx+k)%n;
                int prev_temp = temp;
                temp = grid[next_idx/cols][next_idx%cols];
                grid[next_idx/cols][next_idx%cols] = prev_temp;
                curr_idx = next_idx;
            }
        } 
        return grid;
    }    
};
```
space complexity O (1), time complexity O(N).  
N is mean rows * cols  here. 

# Explanation

The above solution is optimized from following code
```C++
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> answer1(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int k) {
        vector<vector<int>> ans = grid;
        int rows = grid.size(), cols = grid[0].size(), n = rows*cols; 
        for(int curr = 0; curr < n;curr++) { 
            int next = (curr+k)%n;
            ans[next/cols][next%cols]= grid[curr/cols][curr%cols];
        }
        return ans;
    } 
};
```
This code using time O(N) and space O(N). 
And the idea of this code is to represent two dimension into one dimension array. 
Process it in. one dimension array and problem become easy. 

And this is a rorate array problem now. 
Then we need to optimize this solution from this article
https://leetcode.com/problems/rotate-array/discuss/1729976/C%2B%2B-or-O(N)-or-GCD
In this article, it solve rorate array problem by this way. 
```C++
class Solution {
public:
    void rotate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int rows = gcd(n, k);
        for(int i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
            int temp = nums[i];
            int curr_idx = i;                
            for(int j = 0 ; j < n / rows; j++) {
                int next_idx = (curr_idx + k) % n;
                int prev_temp = temp;
                temp = nums[next_idx];
                nums[next_idx] = prev_temp;
                curr_idx = next_idx;
            }
        }   
    }
};
```
Then I adjust this code to become our solution.  
That's how I solve this problem in Time O(N) & Space O(1) in the final solution.

