solutions.content:
It's same idea as 189.rotate array, just convert to grid type!

if we want to take the k last to the begin, we have to do 3 steps:
(1) rotate  whole list
(2) rotate the first k elements
(3) rotate else elements

We can change the position in list to grid by simply divide column number and module column number.


```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> shiftGrid(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int k) {
        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid[0].size();
        k %= n * m;
		// (1) rotate whole list (First half swap with last half)
        for (int i = 0; i < n * m / 2; i++) swap(grid[i/m][i%m], grid[(n*m-1-i)/m][(n*m-1-i)%m]);
		// (2)  rotate the first k elements
        for (int i = 0; i < k / 2; i++) swap(grid[i/m][i%m], grid[(k-1-i)/m][(k-1-i)%m]);
		// (3) rotate else elements
        for (int i = k; i < k + (n * m - k) / 2; i++) swap(grid[i/m][i%m], grid[(n*m-1+k-i)/m][(n*m-1+k-i)%m]);
        return grid;
    }
};
```

