**1-dimensional array index to 2-dimensional array index**
For a given 1-dimensional array element **array[i]**, the corresponding row and column in 2-dimensional array will be **(i / n)** and **(i % n)**, where n is the number of columns of the 2-dimensional array. 

**2-dimensional array index to 1-dimensional array index**
For a given  2-dimensional array element **array[i][j]**, the corresponding index of 1-dimensional array will be **(i * n + j)** , where n is the number of columns of the 2-dimensional array. 

```
public class Solution {
    public IList<IList<int>> ShiftGrid(int[][] grid, int k) {

        int m = grid.Length, n = grid[0].Length, total = m * n; 

        int[][] res = new int[m][];
        for(int i = 0; i < m; i++)
            res[i] = new int[n];

        // convert 2-D array to 1-D array
        for(int pos = 0; pos < total; pos++)
        {
            // new position after shifting k times
            int newPos = (pos + k) % total;       

            // convert 1-D array back to 2-D array
            res[newPos / n][newPos % n] = grid[pos / n][pos % n];
        }

        return res;
    }
}
```


