# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Use **BFS (Level Order Traversal Format)** to assign values to the nodes and store them in an **unordered map** to return the answer in **O(1) time** in the **find() function**.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class FindElements {
public:
    unordered_map<int,bool> mp;
    FindElements(TreeNode* root) {
        queue<pair<TreeNode*,int>> q;
        q.push({root,0});
        while(!q.empty())
        {
            int n = q.size(),f = 1;
            for(int i = 0;i<n;i++)
            {
              TreeNode*  node = q.front().first;
              int val = q.front().second;
              q.pop();
              if(node) mp[val] = true;
             if(node)
             {
                q.push({node->left,2*val+1});
                q.push({node->right,2*val+2});
                f = 0;
             }
             else
             {
                q.push({NULL,2*val+1});
                q.push({NULL,2*val+2});
              }
            }
            if(f) break;
        }  
    }
    bool find(int t) {
         return mp[t]==true;
    }
};
```
