# Approach
Forming a array to store binary tree. The values that is asked to store is similar to index that we use to store element of tree in array. Only storing a tree will take O(n). Otherwise find function will take O(1) time as it is only checking whether at target value, i.e., same as index of array is -1 or not.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$ ---- where n is the number of nodes in tree.

# Code
```
class FindElements {
    vector<int> treeArr;
public:
    FindElements(TreeNode* root) {
        treeArr = vector<int>(1e6+1, -1);
        dfs(root, 0);
    }

    void dfs(TreeNode* root, int i){
        if(root == NULL || i > 1e6)
            return;

        treeArr[i] = i;
        dfs(root->left, 2*i+1);
        dfs(root->right, 2*i+2);
    }

    bool find(int target) {
        if(treeArr[target] == -1)
            return false;

        return true;
    }
};
```

