Let's understand this first. For any integer n, if n mod 3 = 1, then if we subtract n by any integer (smaller than n) m1, m1 mod 3 = 1, then (n-m1) mod 3 = 0. And if we have 2 integer s1 and s2 (s1 and s2 smaller than n), s1 mod 3 = 1 , s2 mod 3 = 1, then (n - s1 - s2) mod 3 = 0. It's the same for n mod 3 = 2
So lets set n as the sum of the input array.
if n%3=1
ans = n - min(m1,s1+ s2)    m1 is the smallest integer that m%3=1 in the list , s1 and s2 are the smallest integers that s or t mod 3 is 2 in the list.

if n%3=2
ans = n - min(m1+m2,s1)     s1 is the smallest integer that m%3=2 in the list , m1 and m2 are the smallest integers that s or t % 3 = 1 in the list.

else
ans = n


