solutions.content:
# Intuition
In order to maximize sum divisible by 3, we need to minimize sum of items, which give the same remainder as the whole array sum.

# Approach
1. Check whole array sum remainder.
- If it is ``0`` then return whole array sum
- Otherwise check the remainder - either ``1`` or ``2``
2. Build two min-heaps for each of the remainders of size ``2``
3. Check different cases for each remainder:
- ``1`` is either smallest remainder-1 value or sum of two smallest remainder-2 values
- ``2`` is either smallest remainder-2 value or sum of two smallest remainder-1 values

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n*log(n))$$

- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution:
    def maxSumDivThree(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        s = sum(nums)
        r = s % 3
        if r == 0:
            return s
        h1, h2 = [], []
        for v in nums:
            if v % 3 == 1:
                if len(h1) < 2:
                    heapq.heappush(h1, -v)
                elif v < -h1[0]:
                    heapq.heappop(h1)
                    heapq.heappush(h1, -v)
            elif v % 3 == 2:
                if len(h2) < 2:
                    heapq.heappush(h2, -v)
                elif v < -h2[0]:
                    heapq.heappop(h2)
                    heapq.heappush(h2, -v)

        r11, r12 = -heapq.heappop(h1) if h1 else s, -heapq.heappop(h1) if h1 else s
        r21, r22 = -heapq.heappop(h2) if h2 else s, -heapq.heappop(h2) if h2 else s

        if r == 1:
            return s - min(r12, r11, r21+r22)

        return s - min(r11 + r12, r22, r21)

