class Solution {
public:
    int maxSumDivThree(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(3,vector<int>(nums.size(),0));
        int state = nums[0]%3;
        for(int i=0;i<3;i++){
            if(i == state){
                dp[i][0] = nums[0];
            }
            else{
                dp[i][0] = 0;
            }
        }

        for(int j=1;j<nums.size();j++){
            for(int i=0;i<3;i++){
                dp[(nums[j] + dp[i][j-1])%3][j] = max(dp[(nums[j] + dp[i][j-1])%3][j], nums[j] + dp[i][j-1]);
            }
            dp[nums[j]%3][j] = max(dp[nums[j]%3][j],nums[j]);
            for(int i=0;i<3;i++){
                dp[i][j] = max(dp[i][j-1],dp[i][j]);
            }
        }
	    return dp[0][nums.size()-1];
}
};
```
In the main loop The following information is stored in dp:
1.There are 3 possibilites for each state `dp[i][j]` where i is the state number and j is the jth index in nums array
2.We take **max** of : a) current nums and each of previous state value and then find the new state into which this whole value will be inserted
b) Exclude current nums and calculate max of a) and previous dp state(`dp[i][j-1]` for my code)
c) Also check if nums[j] itself can go to a state with value higher than a) or b).

