The idea is to store the maximum sum at each position with each mod 0, 1 and 2;
dp[pos][mod] stores the max sum possible till position pos with mod. 
The sum at ith position can be derived by the maximum sum available at i-1th position. 

```
class Solution {
    public int maxSumDivThree(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int[][] dp = new int[n][3];
        dp[0][nums[0]%3] = nums[0];
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++) {
            for(int j=0; j<3; j++) 
                dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j];
            for(int j=0; j<3; j++) {
                int res = dp[i-1][j]+nums[i];
                dp[i][res%3] = Math.max(dp[i][res%3], res);
            }
        }
        return dp[n-1][0];
    }
}
```

