Inspired by https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-moves-to-move-a-box-to-their-target-location/discuss/431528/Python-Dijkstra-Short, here is a Shortest Path Faster Algorithm (modified form of Bellman-Ford, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shortest_Path_Faster_Algorithm).

If we replace the queue with a heap (a hybrid Dijkstra/SPFA) we could get rid of the res and just return moves the first time we reach target.

In any case, I think Dijkstra is the better choice here, as SPFA adds some code complexity (and time complexity) for no gain.

```py
class Solution:
    def minPushBox(self, grid: List[List[str]]) -> int:

        rows, cols = len(grid), len(grid[0])

        free = lambda r, c: 0 <= r < rows and 0 <= c < cols and grid[r][c] != '#'
        box, player, target = [x[1:] for x in sorted((grid[r][c], r, c) for r in range(rows) for c in range(cols) if grid[r][c] in {'S', 'T', 'B'})]

        dist = defaultdict(lambda: float('inf'))
        dist[(player, box)] = 0
        res = float('inf')

        q = {(player, box): None}
        while q:
            player, box = next(iter(q))
            q.pop((player, box))

            if box == target:
                res = min(res, dist[(player, box)])

            for r_offset, c_offset in ((1, 0), (-1, 0), (0, 1), (0, -1)):

                new_player = player[0] + r_offset, player[1] + c_offset
                new_box = box[0] + r_offset, box[1] + c_offset

                if new_player == box and free(*new_box) and dist[(new_player, new_box)] > dist[(player, box)] + 1:
                    dist[(new_player, new_box)] = dist[(player, box)] + 1
                    if (new_player, new_box) not in q:
                        q[(new_player, new_box)] = None

                elif new_player != box and free(*new_player) and dist[(new_player, box)] > dist[(player, box)]:
                    dist[(new_player, box)] = dist[(player, box)]
                    if (new_player, box) not in q:
                        q[(new_player, box)] = None

        return res if res < float('inf') else -1

